description.narrative: By 2019, health facilities are strengthened to equitably provide quality nutrition services., which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022,boys and girls aged 0-59 months, adolescents and women (especially those living in the most disadvantaged communities) have access to basic services, use packages of multisectoral high-impact, gender-sensitive interventions (health /HIV, nutrition, WASH) and adopt appropriate behaviours.

title.narrative: By 2019, health facilities are strengthened to equitably provide quality nutrition services.

description.narrative: In 2019, the treatment capacity of 150 health centres and 109 health posts was strengthened. A total of 497 health workers were trained and now use the new protocol for the care of children. Meanwhile, 11,648 children – girls and boys – were admitted for the treatment of SAM, with a cure rate of over 90%. A network of 800 women's groups supervised by 1,600 leaders whose capacities had been strengthened made it possible to offer integrated nutrition services in support of health centres in the 40 convergence municipalities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
